{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018LN7AYYhJc3xiEXbjhCaUw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pod got killed by the liveness probe while I was trying to exec. Let me wait for it to restart and then quickly get the information I need.\n\nLet me think about what I know so far:\n1. `ping` works without auth - confirmed \n2. The primary issue is `timeoutSeconds: 1` causing timeouts\n3. The verbosity is too high (4) causing overhead\n\nThe fix is clear:\n1. **Increase timeoutSeconds** in both probes (at least 5 seconds)\n2. **Increase failureThreshold** (6 for liveness, 12 for readiness)  \n3. **Increase initialDelaySeconds** (30s for readiness, 60s for liveness)\n4. **Reduce verbosity** in the config map (from 4 to 0)\n5. **Reduce slowOpThresholdMs** (from 1600 to 100)\n\nI also need to account for the OrderedReady pod management policy - pods 1 and 2 won't start until pod 0 is Ready, so I need to make sure all three come up properly. I'll update the ConfigMap to reduce verbosity and fix the probe configuration in the StatefulSet. For the probe command, since `ping` works without authentication, I can use that as the health check. The username is probably `healthuser` based on the secret naming pattern. Since the ping command worked without auth in my test, the real issue is just the timeout being too short—I need to increase it to at least 5 seconds and raise the failure threshold so the probe doesn't kill the pod prematurely. it's probably not profiling much. I should reduce both the verbosity to 0 and the slowOpThresholdMs to 100 to cut down on unnecessary logging and I/O overhead. Once I fix these timeout and threshold values and get the pods running, I can then verify the health user setup and update the probes accordingly. I'll patch the StatefulSet right away with the timeout and failure threshold adjustments, then wait for the pods to stabilize and verify the replica status. For the probe command, I'll include the health user credentials by referencing them from the secret as an environment variable to ensure authentication works properly.\n\nActually, I'm realizing that environment variable substitution doesn't work directly in exec probes since they run without shell expansion. I'd need to wrap it in a shell script to use the variable, but that adds overhead. Given that the ping command already works without authentication based on my earlier testing, I'll stick with the simpler approach and just improve the timing parameters instead.\n\nLet me adjust the timeout and failure thresholds to give the probe more breathing room, and also dial back the verbose logging that might be slowing things down. Before making credential changes, I should verify whether the health user actually exists in the database—if it doesn't, adding auth will just cause the probe to fail. My plan is to first fix the timing issues to get the pods stable, then check the user situation, and only then consider adding credentials if needed.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":518,"cache_read_input_tokens":35548,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":518},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"16475930-95c6-4161-b65c-95830795d655","uuid":"182e2c46-44fe-4a4c-89bb-5c89bfe618f6","request_id":"req_011CcgfFX8uGaisM6i8bczLP"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018LN7AYYhJc3xiEXbjhCaUw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The pod was killed by liveness. The root problems are clear:\n1. `timeoutSeconds: 1` — mongosh startup alone takes >1s, causing timeout\n2. `failureThreshold: 2` — too aggressive, kills pods before MongoDB can initialize\n3. `verbosity: 4` in config — excessive debug logging creating I/O overhead\n4. `initialDelaySeconds` too short for a MongoDB replica set to initialize\n\nLet me fix both the ConfigMap and the StatefulSet probes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":518,"cache_read_input_tokens":35548,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":518},"output_tokens":22,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"16475930-95c6-4161-b65c-95830795d655","uuid":"03bcd065-3d1a-49e1-93ed-54dab65ae460","request_id":"req_011CcgfFX8uGaisM6i8bczLP"}
